{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian_energyEigenstate\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">hamiltonian_energyEigenstate</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.QuantaWaveNumber\">QuantaWaveNumber</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian\">hamiltonian</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate\">energyEigenstate</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenvalue\">energyEigenvalue</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSMul.hSMul\">•</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate\">energyEigenstate</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The energy eigenstates satisfy the time-independent Schrodinger equation. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian_energyEigenstate","kind":"theorem","line":592,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian_energyEigenstate","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L592-L644"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenvalue\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">energyEigenvalue</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.QuantaWaveNumber\">QuantaWaveNumber</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The energy eigenvalue of the tight binding chain for a `k` in `QuantaWaveNumber` is\n`E0 - 2 * t * Real.cos (k * T.a)`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenvalue","kind":"def","line":581,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenvalue","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L581-L584"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate_orthogonal\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">energyEigenstate_orthogonal</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Pairwise.html#Pairwise\">Pairwise</a> <span class=\"fn\">fun (<span class=\"fn\">k1</span> <span class=\"fn\">k2</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.QuantaWaveNumber\">QuantaWaveNumber</a></span></span>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/Defs.html#Inner.inner\">inner</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate\">energyEigenstate</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k1</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate\">energyEigenstate</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">k2</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The energy eigenstates of the tight binding chain are orthogonal.\n\nThis is a fundamental quantum mechanical result: eigenstates of a Hermitian operator\n(the Hamiltonian) with distinct eigenvalues are orthogonal. Here we prove it directly\nusing the periodic boundary conditions which quantize the wavenumbers.\n\nThe key physical insight is that different wavenumbers k₁ ≠ k₂ give rise to different\nN-th roots of unity exp(i(k₂-k₁)a), and the sum of all N-th roots of unity equals zero. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate_orthogonal","kind":"theorem","line":507,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate_orthogonal","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L507-L573"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">energyEigenstate</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.QuantaWaveNumber\">QuantaWaveNumber</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.HilbertSpace\">HilbertSpace</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The energy eigenstates of the tight binding chain They are given by\n`∑ n, exp (I * k * n * T.a) • |n⟩`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate","kind":"def","line":496,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.energyEigenstate","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L496-L499"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.quantaWaveNumber_exp_add_one\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">quantaWaveNumber_exp_add_one</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Fin\">Fin</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.N\">N</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.QuantaWaveNumber\">QuantaWaveNumber</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Complex.exp\">Complex.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex.I\">Complex.I</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">k</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.a\">a</a></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a>   <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Complex.exp\">Complex.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex.I\">Complex.I</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">k</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">n</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.a\">a</a></span></span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Exponential.html#Complex.exp\">Complex.exp</a> (<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex.I\">Complex.I</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">k</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.a\">a</a></span></span>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.quantaWaveNumber_exp_add_one","kind":"theorem","line":476,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.quantaWaveNumber_exp_add_one","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L476-L482"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<s