r.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian\">hamiltonian</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">φ</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The hamiltonian of the tight binding chain is hermitian. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian_hermitian","kind":"theorem","line":222,"name":"CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian_hermitian","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L222-L244"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.hamiltonian\"><span class=\"name\">CondensedMatter</span>.<span class=\"name\">TightBindingChain</span>.<span class=\"name\">hamiltonian</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">T</span> : <a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain\">TightBindingChain</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.HilbertSpace\">HilbertSpace</a></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">→ₗ[</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Complex/Basic.html#Complex\">ℂ</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Module/LinearMap/Defs.html#LinearMap\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">T</span>.<a href=\"./PhysLean/CondensedMatter/TightBindingChain/Basic.html#CondensedMatter.TightBindingChain.HilbertSpace\">HilbertSpace</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The Hamiltonian of the tight binding chain with periodic\nboundary conditions is given by `E₀ ∑ n, |n⟩⟨n| - t ∑ n, (|n⟩⟨n + 1| + |n + 1⟩⟨n|)`.\nThe periodic boundary conditions is manifested by the `+` in `n + 1` being\nwithin `Fin T.N` (that is modulo `T.